////Sternoclavicular joint

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft tissue of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Sternoclavicular joint' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Activated osteoarthritis' radio button is enabled
And 'Inflammation' radio button is enabled
And 'Luxation' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Activated osteoarthritis' radio button
Then 'Sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Inflammation' radio button
Then 'Erosions' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Luxation' radio button
Then 'Rupture sternoclavicular ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tear Discus articularis' checkbox is enabled
